# Fluff Date: 2026-02-16 11:04:06
overview:<p>The Beowulf was designed in the late 3050s as a ComStar initiative to replace the Mongoose reconnaissance 'Mechs lost when Terra fell to the Word of Blake in 3058. Rather than attempt to procure more of the centuries-old Mongoose design, the Precentor Martial commissioned an entirely new scout 'Mech that would address the older platform's chronic shortcomings in firepower and survivability. Odin Manufacturing's facility on Orestes, one of several small production sites ComStar had been upgrading in the Free Rasalhague Republic since the Battle of Tukayyid, was selected to produce the new design. At forty-five tons, the Beowulf was nearly twice the mass of its predecessor, representing a deliberate shift toward a heavier, more capable scout platform. First entering service in 3059, the Beowulf proved successful enough that its chassis eventually formed the basis for several variants and the Clan-technology Beowulf IIC developed for the Ghost Bear Dominion.</p>

capabilities:<p>The Beowulf achieves its reconnaissance mission through a combination of speed, advanced electronics, and sufficient firepower to fight its way out of contact. A GM 270 XL engine drives the chassis to speeds approaching one hundred kilometers per hour, while a MASC system can push that to nearly one hundred and thirty in short bursts, allowing the Beowulf to keep pace with most light 'Mechs. Six Odin Type II jump jets provide one hundred and eighty meters of jump capability for navigating rough terrain, giving the design excellent tactical flexibility.</p><p>The Beowulf's electronics suite is particularly noteworthy for a medium scout. A Beagle active probe detects hidden units while a TAG system allows the 'Mech to designate targets for Arrow IV artillery strikes, making it as much a force multiplier as a direct combatant. Primary armament consists of a Blankenburg large pulse laser supported by two Diverse Optics extended-range medium lasers, providing accurate firepower at medium ranges. Eight and a half tons of Wall Type 6 ferro-fibrous armor offer respectable protection for a medium scout, though the XL engine remains the design's most significant vulnerability, concentrated torso damage can disable the 'Mech far more quickly than its armor coverage might suggest.</p>

deployment:<p>Introduced during the Jihad, the BEO-14 represents a significant departure from the original scout-focused design, reconfiguring the Beowulf for close-quarters combat. The large pulse laser and one extended-range medium laser give way to a pair of medium variable speed pulse lasers and a combination of extended-range small lasers, a standard small laser, and a 'Mech-scale sword. Triple Strength Myomer replaces the MASC system, providing both enhanced melee capability and a speed boost when the 'Mech runs hot. A C3 slave unit integrates the variant into network-centric formations, while the deliberate reduction in heat sink capacity helps the TSM activate more readily. This variant was produced through the Arcturan Arms Refit Facility on Arcturus.</p>

history:<p>The Beowulf's origins trace directly to ComStar's loss of Terra in 3058. When the Word of Blake seized humanity's homeworld, ComStar's entire inventory of Mongoose reconnaissance 'Mechs was either destroyed or captured. The Precentor Martial's decision to commission a purpose-built replacement rather than source existing designs reflected both the urgency of the need and ComStar's confidence in its growing manufacturing capability within the Free Rasalhague Republic.</p><p>Odin Manufacturing's facility on Orestes had been among several small production sites that ComStar began upgrading into full 'Mech factories after the Clan defeat on Tukayyid. The Beowulf was the first new 'Mech design to emerge from this investment. Initial production was split between the Com Guards and the Rasalhague KungsArmé, with the 321st Division of the Com Guards and the Fourth Kavalleri of the KungsArmé among the first units to receive the new 'Mech.</p><p>The Jihad and its aftermath dramatically altered the Beowulf's trajectory. As Clan Ghost Bear absorbed the Free Rasalhague Republic to form the Ghost Bear Dominion, Odin Manufacturing's relationship with the Clan deepened. This led to increasingly ambitious Clan-technology refits of the Beowulf chassis during the 3070s, though persistent electronics incompatibilities between Inner Sphere and Clan systems plagued these early hybrid designs. Meanwhile, Lyran interests produced the BEO-14 melee variant through the Arcturan Arms Refit Facility on Arcturus, while ComStar pursued the experimental BEO-X-7a stealth prototype using partially assembled Odin chassis. Odin's increasing focus on Clan-technology production ultimately culminated in the purpose-built Beowulf IIC, effectively superseding the original Inner Sphere design within the Dominion's touman.</p>

